trans-unit.source: Provides data for the <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.Integration.WindowsFormsHost.ChildChanged"></xref> and <xref href="System.Windows.Forms.Integration.ElementHost.ChildChanged"></xref> events.

The ChildChangedEventArgs class is used by the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.WindowsFormsHost> and <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.ElementHost> classes when the values of the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.WindowsFormsHost.Child%2A?displayProperty=fullName> or <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.ElementHost.Child%2A?displayProperty=fullName> properties change.
trans-unit.target: Klasa ChildChangedEventArgs jest używana przez <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.WindowsFormsHost>i <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.ElementHost>klasy, gdy wartości <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.WindowsFormsHost.Child%2A?displayProperty=fullName>lub <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.ElementHost.Child%2A?displayProperty=fullName>zmiany właściwości.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.ElementHost.Child%2A?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.WindowsFormsHost.Child%2A?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.ElementHost> </xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.WindowsFormsHost>

trans-unit.source: Use the <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.ChildChangedEventArgs.PreviousChild%2A> property to get the previously assigned child control or element.
trans-unit.target: Użyj <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.ChildChangedEventArgs.PreviousChild%2A>właściwości kontrolki podrzędnej poprzednio przypisanych lub element.</xref:System.Windows.Forms.Integration.ChildChangedEventArgs.PreviousChild%2A>
